com.github.arachnidium.model.common

Class Application<S extends Handle,U extends IHowToGetHandle>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.arachnidium.model.abstractions.ModelObject<S>
      • com.github.arachnidium.model.common.Application<S,U>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - It means that objects can be stationed on browser window or mobile application screen. As for application it means the first or the single (main) Handle is a BrowserWindow or MobileScreen. And all child (decomposition) objects are on BrowserWindow or(/and) MobileScreen.
    If there is <S extends Handle> or <Handle> it means that both BrowserWindow and MobileScreen are possible. It is good for situations when interaction with UI of browser client and the perfectly similar mobile client has to be automated.
    If it needs to be bounded by only one Handle subclass ( BrowserWindow or MobileScreen) then

    <BrowserWindow> only browser windows
    or
    <MobileScreen> only mobile screens
    U - It means the way of getting decomposable parts of the application. It needs to be used when it is possible the interaction with more than one window or mobile screen/context at the same time. Possible strategies are HowToGetBrowserWindow and HowToGetMobileScreen If there is <S extends IHowToGetHandle> or <IHowToGetHandle> it means that both strategies are possible. It is good for situations when interaction with UI of browser client and the perfectly similar mobile client has to be automated.

    Also, it can be useful when it needs to bind some decomposition parts to concrete URLs/Android activities, page titles/context names etc.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDestroyable, IDecomposable, IDecomposableByHandles<U>, org.openqa.selenium.internal.WrapsDriver
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BrowserApplication, MobileApplication

    public abstract class Application<S extends Handle,U extends IHowToGetHandle>
extends ModelObject<S>
implements IDecomposableByHandles<U>
    The Common representation of any application. Using it you can model automated interaction with application as with a complex aggregated object.
    It is implemented as a factory by default.

      • getPart

        public <T extends IDecomposable> T getPart(Class<T> partClass,
                                           HowToGetByFrames path,
                                           org.openqa.selenium.By by)
        Gets a representation of UI or some logically final piece of UI. It is general UI or its peace which is inside frame (frame, iframe, etc). It is actual for browser and mobile hybrid UI.

        The root element where this UI is located is known.
